Although the capability of this coronavirus to bind particulate matters remains to be established, chronic exposure to atmospheric contamination and related diseases may represent a risk factor in determining the severity of Covid-19 syndrome and the high incidence of fatal events (
 Chen et al., 2020; 
 Conticini et al., 2020; 
 Dutheil et al., 2020; 
 Wang et al., 2020a; 
 Wu et al., 2020).
